    "en": {
      "title": "Minister's announcement on wheat flour",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trade and Food Security Minister Nalin Fernando said that there will be no shortage of wheat flour in the future and there is no need to increase the price of wheat flour.",
        "The Minister disclosed the above during a discussion held today (05) at the Ministry of Commerce between the Minister and representatives of the All Sri Lanka Bakery Owners Association.",
        "The minister pointed out that he was informed during a meeting held last Friday with two leading wheat flour companies in Sri Lanka that he has enough stock to produce wheat flour for one month.",
        "The minister mentioned that wheat flour has been imported from Turkey and Dubai and is expected to be distributed by September 15.",
        "Considering this matter, the minister said that there will be no shortage of flour and there is no need to increase the price of wheat flour and there is no need for a control price.",
        "The Minister also said that the officials of the Ministry of Commerce will provide a written report on the demand of wheat flour for local consumption for the next six months.",
        "According to this, the minister mentioned that the wheat flour companies have been requested to distribute the required quantity of wheat flour to the market for future consumption and to increase the production capacity."
      ],
